\section{Modularity}{


\strong{\code{ramp.xds}} is designed for modular computation. The
mathematical framework has
five core biological processes organized
into three chunks called \strong{dynamical components} (see \link{xds_info_dynamical_components}).
The modular design
makes it possible to build models that fully define all
components (using \link{xds_setup}), or to
develop systems of equations to isolate and study some part
of a system.

To implement \emph{plug-and-play} modularity, a trivial module was developed
for each component:
a \emph{trace function} in
the trivial \emph{upstream} component is configured to pass known inputs (see \link{xds_info_trivial_forcing}).
}

